column5: Well gang, I know I haven't been around much for the last few months, working on a computer for 8-10 hours a day, by the time I get home at night the last thing I want to do is sit down in front of my computer.  Just wanted to let you know, I haven't forgotten about any of you!  I am leaving tomorrow morning early for North Myrtle Beach and won't be back until the end of Jan.. Hope to come back all rested and ready to go again with my batteries recharged.  Take care of each other, play nice, be safe! I'll check in if I get a chance to, otherwise, see you all at the end of the month.  P.S.  I still haven't gotten any offers of food donations for the Tyler G2G so pleas, if you can help out post here or email me at home.
Good Luck and have a great time on holiday Cliff! I was wondering about you the other day.  Happy New Year!  Whopper
You and Sue have the best time, Bud. And no, we don't really need any Speedo pics.
Enjoy the trip Cliff. I was wondering where you got to as I hadn't seen you here for a while.
Have a great time Cliff and Sue.  I will see if I can get something from M&M's or maybe Costco?  Maureen
Have a GRR R R R  R   E   A   T trip, and enjoy yourselves down there. wanna take the boat up to Jack's when you come back for crappie? Not likely will have safe ice!
.....Have a great holiday Sue and Cliff.
Hope your taking your golf clubs ?
Maribeth and I wish you and Sue a great holiday...  You sure deserve one...  BTW...did I ever mention that ''work'' is a four-letter word
Have a great vacation Cliff. Relax. Enjoy. Have a drink or two. Lay in the sun. You know the drill. We'll see you when you return.

I was wondering where you disappeared to big guy. Nice to see you're still keeping an eye on us.  Have yourself a great vacation and see if you can bring us back some picturs of fish. We kinda like that stuff round here.
